‹?datasetreadme-sourceC:\Users\Toka\Documents\Codex\2026-05-01\donne-moi-des-id-es-de\.atlastrace\cases\correlation-demo\artifacts\2026-05-01T08-40-37+00-00-README.mddcc28c43a4faedeb8f3059fb503d57ec9c155593a9a57c881a8228b96799e64e{"artifact_label": "readme-source", "mime_type": "text/markdown", "original_path": "C:\\Users\\Toka\\Documents\\Codex\\2026-05-01\\donne-moi-des-id-es-de\\README.md", "size_bytes": 6643, "text_preview": "# AtlasTrace AtlasTrace is a massive Python multitool for passive OSINT work, investigation case management, evidence capture, entity graphing, document and media triage, archive workflows, breach checks, and cross-source correlation reporting. The goal is to combine the best parts of: - a caseboard - a public-source collection pipeline - a lightweight evidence locker - a graph of people, organizations, domains, handles, files, and URLs - a correlation engine that cross-references one dataset..."}2026-05-01T08:40:37+00:00‡V )‚/
